The paper proposes a new unsupervised learning method for constructing sparse, non-linear, high-dimensional representations of input data. This makes it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The method is tested on vision datasets, indicating a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of the method on gene expression data, suggesting a potential application in bioinformatics (cs.NE) and systems biology (cs.SI).
